FT  03 MAR 93 / World News in Brief: Harrods bomb suspects arrested in armed
raid
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Two men were being questioned about the IRA bombing of Harrods in January
after an armed raid last night on a house in Stoke Newington, north London,
hours after a police video of two suspects was shown on television. Scotland
Yard said shots were fired at anti-terrorist squad detectives and a tactical
firearms unit during the raid. Police did not return fire. Firearms and
explosives were recovered from the house.
