<HEADLINE>
FT  03 MAR 93 / Clarke outlines proposals for young offenders
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
New secure training centres for 12-15-year-olds - part of a government
response to mounting public concern about juvenile crime - may be operated
by the private sector, the public sector or voluntary organisations.
Mr Kenneth Clarke, home secretary, in a joint news conference with health
secretary Virginia Bottomley yesterday, said that all three sectors will be
invited to bid to operate the centres, which would be 'different from
anything that has been offered before'. About six centres, providing
accommodation for up to 300 persistent reoffenders, are likely to be
developed initially.
