<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAR 93 / Management (The Growing Business): Checking out your bank
account - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ninety-five per cent of business bank accounts contain errors, according to
a survey of 152 accounts carried out by Bankchek, a specialist consultancy.
It found that in 75 cases banks had overcharged their customers, while in 70
they had undercharged. Only seven accounts were correct. The average amount
overcharged was Pounds 1,412 a year while the undercharging amounted to
Pounds 956.
Bankchek ascribed the high error rate to poor administrative systems.
</TEXT>
