<TEXT>
Yugoslav peace talks are scheduled to resume at the United Nations today
provided all the main participants show up, Reuter reports from the UN.
They are to focus on a plan and map drafted by the co-chairmen of the
international conference on the former Yugoslavia, Mr Cyrus Vance,
representing the UN, and Lord Owen, on behalf of the European Community.
