with Moslems majorities, three Serb, two Croat and two mixed.
Bosnian Serb chief Radovan Karadzic was due to arrive in New York yesterday
apparently satisfied he would not be impeded by a private lawsuit brought
against him during his previous stay by organisations acting on behalf of
two victims of alleged atrocities by Serb forces in Bosnia.
