</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Never underestimate the ability of a computer to offer fresh insights into
investment conditions. A fund manager was checking a document discussing
prospects for rental growth in the UK property market when the computer
flashed up the following query: 'Rent review'. Is this a mistake? Is it the
expression rigor mortis?
